  <body
    style="width:800px; margin:50px auto;font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;"
  >
    <table
      style="border:1px solid #dddddd;width:100%;border-collapse: collapse;"
    >
      <tr><td
         style="text-align:center;background-image: url('{{websiteMailBgUrl}}'); background-size: cover;background-position: center;padding:10px"
        >
        <img src="{{websiteLogoUrl}}" alt="XDS-SPARK" width="150" />
        </td></tr>
      <tr>
        <td style="padding:0 20px">
          <p style="padding-top:10px">Hi {{firstName}},</p>
          <p>
            We see that you have upgraded to an XDS Spark Premium membership - congratulations! You are unlocking rich functionality that is sure to support your external development needs.
          </p>
          <p>As you experience the new Premium account, consider exploring the following areas.</p>
          <ul>
            <li style="padding-bottom: 10px;"><b>View Full Service Provider Profiles -</b> View complete Service Provider profiles including portfolios, project highlights, certification and due diligence info, and contact partners as needed.</li>
            <li style="padding-bottom: 10px;">
              <b>Partner Relationship Management -</b> Inside a Service Provider profile, go to the <b>My Spark</b> tab to manage personalized information that <u>only you can see.</u>.
              <ul type="circle">
                <li><b>Partner Status -</b> indicating the service provider’s ability to work with your company</li>
                <li><b>Rates -</b> track day and monthly rates by service with notes, and post a rate card</li>
                <li><b>Performance -</b> track project performance by quality, on-time delivery and communication</li>
                <li><b>Notes -</b> Post notes from meetings, or other important information on your partners</li>
              </ul>
            </li>
            <li style="padding-bottom: 10px;"><b>Company Administration -</b> As a Premium member, you can assign up to four (4) user licenses to colleagues in your organization, and manage these accounts. Go to “Company Admin” in the navigation menu to get started!</li>
            <li style="padding-bottom: 10px;"><b>Post Opportunities -</b> Use Post Opportunities to share an upcoming project in order to discover new Service Provider candidates. Your post can be <b>anonymous</b>, and will only be published to Service Providers whose skills match that of your needs.</li>
            <li style="padding-bottom: 10px;"><b>Compare Service Providers -</b> Use the Compare feature to place up to 10 Service Providers side-by-side in order to evaluate strengths and gaps.</li>
            <li style="padding-bottom: 10px;"><b>Follow Profiles -</b>Find a new Service Provider you find interesting? Hit the Follow button on their profile to receive weekly notifications when they update their Portfolio, Project Highlights and Due Diligence information.</li>
            <li style="padding-bottom: 10px;"><b>My Lists -</b> Build shareable lists of Service Providers any way you want, and track and maintain these over time.</li>
            <li style="padding-bottom: 10px;"><b>My Projects -</b> Create projects and add lists of candidate Service Providers. Share projects with your teams to determine partners that are the best fit for engagements.</li>
            <li><b>Events -</b> Interested in seeing which Service Providers will be at your next event? Use the Events filter to show a listing of partners you may want to meet with on site.</li>
          </ul>
          <p>We hope that you enjoy your journey using XDS Spark!</p>
